**who —** Byte-Pair Encoding — how the pieces are learned · electrical

**what —** how the pieces are learned · electrical

**where —** TOK · THE TOKENIZER (niphelektron · the inference pipeline)  Framework inputs: stream; token; vector  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** The dominant method: start from single characters and repeatedly merge the most frequent adjacent pair into a new token, until the vocabulary is full. The common gets short, the rare stays long — learned from the corpus, not designed.

**how —** Rendered from the public record.

**◌ the mythos —** The dominant method: start from single characters and repeatedly merge the most frequent adjacent pair into a new token, until the vocabulary is full. The common gets short, the rare stays long — learned from the corpus, not designed. a part of the inference pipeline

